		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="aling(right)"><placeName>Charleston S. C.</placeName> <date>March 3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> 5627</date></p>
				<p>My dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have the honor to enclose you the<lb/> copy of the Resolutions unanimously adopted by the Board of<lb/> Trustees at a regular meeting convened this day.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Permit me to add&#44; that they embody the<lb/> earnest convictions&#44; and sincere wishes&#44; not only of the<lb/> Board of Trustees&#44; but of all the members of our<lb/> community&#44; who unite with me in the sincere<lb/> prayer&#44; that the God of <placeName>Israel</placeName> will grant you renewed<lb/> health and strength&#44; and length of days&#44; to officiate in<lb/> your sacred functions.</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">With sincere regard</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">I remain very respy</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">Nathaniel Levine</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Secy &#38; <add>&#63;</add> KKBE</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">Extract from the minutes</p>
				<p rend="align(center)">x  x  x  x  x  x  x</p>
				<p>At a regular meeting of the Board of Trustees K. K. B.<lb/> Elohim convened at the Vestry room <date>Sunday Adar 23rd<lb/> 5627</date>&#44; the following Resolutions were unanimously adopted.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Whereas&#44; the members of this Board have heard with<lb/> great satisfaction the very eloquent sermons delivered by<lb/> the <persName>Revd. Isaac Leeser</persName>&#44; in our Synagogue&#44; during the<lb/> past two weeks&#59; and although we are sensible that no<lb/> words of praise coming from any quarter can increase<lb/> the fame of&#44; or add honor to&#44; that distinguished &#8220;light<lb/> in <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#8221;&#44; Nevertheless&#44; we feel it due to ourselves<lb/> and to the Congregators whom we represpent&#44; to place<lb/> on record our appreciation of his efforts&#44; therefore</p>
				<p>Resolved&#44; That the thanks of this Board are hereby<lb/> tendered to the <persName>Revd. Isaac Leeser</persName> for the valuable<lb/>  moral and religious teachings with which he has<lb/> favored our congregation during his brief sojourn<lb/> among us.</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>Resolved&#44; That we hope his health may be<lb/> improved by his visit to the <placeName>South</placeName>&#44; and that<lb/> he may be spared for many years to preach and<lb/> teach the words of truth and pure Jewish doctrine.</p>
				<p>Resolved&#44; That a copy of these Resolutions be<lb/> sent to the Revd. Gentleman and that they be<lb/> published in the &#8220;Occident&#8221; &#38; &#8220;Jewish Messenger&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">Nathl. Levine</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Secy &#38; Trease KKBE</p>
			
